good advice for a soon to be college freshman im abnout to be a college freshmen any advice make friends or at least be on good terms with your ra ca don't be the loud neighbor who always has their music blaring unless you're sleeping changing clothes really trying to concentrate leave the door to your dorm room open so that people can stop in and say hi join a club student organization to meet people make friends with at least one person in every class you take so that if you miss class because you're sick hungover didn't feel like going etc you can still get the notes don't overwhelm yourself with classes each semester college isn't just about studying make sure you have sandals for the showers and a plastic basket to carry all your shower stuff in make a homemade meal every once in a while my friends and i planned a big themed dinner every month my freshman year don't be afraid to ask for help in a class visit your professor during his or her office hours even if you don't have a question about the material if you're going to drink don't do it in the dorms loft your bed because dorm rooms are tiny and at least this way you have a little more room don't live with a friend it can ruin the friendship find out if other people from your high school are going to be there so that you'll at least know someone there email if you have anymore questions good luck One Tree Hill (TV series) The Catcher in the Rye Dormitory Brown University Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Freed-Hardeman University Shaggy dog story Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Georgia Institute of Technology Franklin W. Olin College of Engineering Phillips Exeter Academy University of Massachusetts Amherst Connecticut College New York University The Inside Undergrads University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill Claremont McKenna College Student Williams College Social rule Futurama (TV series - season 2) Ohio Wesleyan University Harvey Mudd College Little Britain Rent (musical) Episodes of Lost (Season